The report prepared by Estonian shipping experts who examined the Discovery film material before its release shows that there are more injuries in the hull of the sunken ferry Estonia than just one large hole.
The report was presented to the government, which has so far only talked about one large hole that needs to be investigated.
Before the film was released, the authors showed the footage filmed underwater to Mart Luik, an advisor to the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, and Estonian shipping experts.
Based on what they saw in Oslo, the experts prepared a report which, in addition to the four-meter-high and one-point-two-meter-wide hole shown in the film, also mentions another tear-like injury on the same side.
Mart Luik said he did not see this second injury as he was giving an interview to a journalist at the same time.
There, they first saw the seabed, which is actually a rocky surface, not as the filmmakers claimed, right? And they also saw the injury, which was shown in that part of the film.
The black material of the film was only shown to the Estonian experts who went on the trip.
The filmmakers then invited the four of us, who were involved as experts, to their computer and showed us an additional video clip that was not included in the series, where another injury could be seen.
They said they were showing it to us before the premiere just for information.
The report was presented to the government, which has so far only mentioned one large hole.
In their short report, they did mention a few sentences to the government.
But why has the government been saying all along that there is only one hole and they have not mentioned any other damages?
Certainly, it is central, undoubtedly there is one hole, that was actually described in those frames, I think that what the witnesses saw, I think, those experts who saw those frames, I think it is reasonable for them to speak to the public about it, there is nothing to practice here.
The experts themselves have not previously referred to other injuries at the request of the Norwegian filming crew.
Since they asked us not to talk about this additional material, it was our opportunity to tell them about it first, but since these speculations have quickly surfaced, it now seems that this additional video material filmed underwater is crucial evidence that should come out.
Discovery informed ERR today in writing that, according to the government's request, they will provide Estonia with the black material, and Discovery also acknowledged that, in addition to the hole, they discovered other stone boxes in Keres, but the series only shows discoveries that the authors considered journalistically important.
And we now have Tallinn University of Technology senior researcher and shipbuilding doctor Kristjan Tabri in the studio, good evening.
Good evening.
Can we now confidently say that the documentary makers lied and did not reveal the full truth?
I cannot answer that question exactly, what their motives were, to reveal something, not to reveal something, but obviously we have seen materials that have a great weight as industrial material, so in that sense, yes, it would have been correct to present these materials in this field.
Let's talk specifically about what else was in those materials, what other injuries could be seen after Estonia?
We saw an unofficial clip, about fifteen to twenty seconds, which was allegedly taken from Estonia during the same filming, where you could see the seabed, which was rather rocky, and you could also see a relatively large injury on the stern of the ship.
So in addition to what is currently being talked about.
Yes, in addition to that. Am I understanding correctly that it may not have been filmed at Estonia at all, when you said that the fifteen seconds were allegedly filmed there?
Well, we have seen that surface for maybe twenty seconds in those videos, so it is difficult to give a conclusive answer, but what can be seen and what is actually visible in the video that has been made public, is that the seabed is quite hard.
And the injuries are caused by what?
I would still dare to guess that these injuries are due to the fact that the ship is on its side on the seabed, on a relatively hard surface, which is obviously uneven terrain.
And the ship, as I understand it, has started to sink according to the experts' assessment.
Well, they also claim in the series that allegedly during their filming they also identified the current angle of the ship, the angle of the keel, which differs by twelve degrees from what was registered after the accident.
So in the video, there are two injuries visible, one near the letter "e" and the other on the stern side. In your opinion, is it possible that there are more ruptures there?
Well, I haven't seen any other ruptures directly, I would also say from the published materials, there are actually other dents visible, which are no longer in contact with the ground, but where there is clearly a paint damage, which has probably occurred in contact with the ground, but I wouldn't exclude that there may be a third or fourth opening somewhere.
This second hole or rupture, how to call it, on the stern side, is it now higher or lower than the first one?
It is very difficult for us to speculate about the location of this opening, where it is, it seemed to be near the stabilizer, near the stabilizer, significantly on the stern side, probably also from the S-wave inscription on the stern side, but I assume that it is roughly at the same height as the first opening, above the impact beam.
Finally, as a scientist, these holes have not been created by a collision with an unknown object.
It is very difficult to construct a scenario where two openings of this size are created with such a distance, it is very likely that these openings were created on the seabed.
And finally, in your opinion, is it necessary to initiate a new investigation or even, for example, to raise the Estonia?
I think that raising it is definitely not reasonable, with today's technology we can get a lot of information from the seabed.
It is difficult for me to assess how much this new opening will reveal, it will be revealed, and whether it will increase the number of believers in the official report or not, and it is certainly possible to explain why these openings have occurred.
It seems that it is still unclear whether the official theory is believed, that if water enters from a foreign object, the ship will sink, then it would also be possible to show with modern methods during the investigation that a ship in such a situation would sink.
Kristjan Tabri, thank you for these comments.
Thank you.
